{{unreferenced|date=February 2013}} {{Infobox park | name = Danube-Ipoly National Park | photo = | photo_width = | photo_alt = | photo_caption = [[Rosalia longicorn]], the mascot of the park | type = National Park | location = [[Hungary]] | coords = {{Coord|47|46|N|18|57|E|type:landmark_region:HU|display=title,inline}} | area = {{convert|603.14|km2|abbr=on}} | created = {{Start date|1997}} | operator = National Parks Directorate | visitation_num = | status = Open | open = | website = [http://www.dinpi.hu www.dinpi.hu] }}
'''Danube-Ipoly National Park''' is one of the most diverse [[national park]]s in [[Hungary]]. In 1997, the park was created from Pilis and Börzsöny national parks, with the addition of part of the [[floodplain]] of the [[River Ipoly]]. This park encompasses areas in [[Budapest]], [[Pest County]], [[Komárom-Esztergom County]] and [[Fejér County]]. Its offices are in Budapest and in the [[Jókai garden]] (Budapest XII), and its headquarters are in [[Esztergom]].
Some species &ndash; both flora and fauna &ndash; have their sole habitat in this park, and there is a programme to save these rare and endangered species.
