[[File:Danmark før 1645.png|thumb|Denmark before 1645]]
'''Eastdenmark''' ({{lang-da|Østdanmark}}) is a geographical term that refers to the part of [[Denmark]] east of Storebælt, including [[Zealand (Denmark)|Zealand]] and [[Bornholm]]. From a linguistic and historical point of view the term refers to the area east of the [[Øresund]] (the former Danish territories [[Scania]], [[Halland]] and [[Blekinge]] and Bornholm).<ref>Jens Christian Vesterskov Johansen: ''Da Østdanmark blev Sydsverige. Otte studier i dansk-svenske relationer i 1600-tallet'', Ebeltoft 2003, {{ISBN|8789224744}}</ref> The former dialects in [[Skåneland]] are accordingly called East Danish (''Østdansk'').

