'''Indawgyi Lake Wildlife Sanctuary''' is a wildlife reserve of [[Burma]]. It is located in [[Mohnyin Township]] in [[Kachin State]]. It occupies an area of {{convert|299.32|sqmi|km2|sigfig=3}} and was established in 1999. The Ministry of Forestry of Myanmar Government announced [[Indawgyi Lake]] with surface area {{Convert|64003|acre|ha}} and five surrounding forest reserves with the area of {{Convert|137386|acre|ha}}, totaling {{Convert|201389|acre|ha}} as “Inndawgyi Lake Sanctuary” with the Notification No (39/2004) dated 9-8-2004; On 18 December 2003, it was recognized as ASEAN Heritage Park. The region is home to rare bird species and other wild animals including wild elephants, bantengs and gaurs, rare gibbon species and forest birds.<ref>http://www.mrtv3.net.mm/newpaper/209newsn.pdf{{Dead link|date=November 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }} Page 11 Column 2</ref>

The {{Convert|65|mi|km|adj=mid|long}} ring-road of Indawgyi consists of <ref>http://www.mrtv3.net.mm/newpaper/2110newsn.pdf{{dead link|date=July 2016 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }} Page 9 Col 2&3</ref>
* Nantmong Village to Nyaungbin Village {{Convert|25|mi|km}}
* Nyaungbin Village to Chaungwa-Mana Khaw Village {{Convert|22|mi|km}}
* Mana Khaw Village to Nantmong Village {{Convert|18|mi|km}}

