[[File:Pettarra kokapena.png|thumb|150 px|Petarra in Zuberoa]] '''Pettarra''' ([[Basque language|Basque]], /petjara/, from beheretar(ra)[[Asterisk|*]] 'lowlander', {{lang-fr|Basse-Soule}}), was the vernacular name for the area along the lower course of the [[Saison (river)|Saison]] ([[French Basque Country]]), as opposed to the [[Basabürüa]].<ref>Jean-Baptiste Orpustan, ''Nouvelle toponymie basque'', Presses Universitaires de Bordeaux, {{ISBN|2-86781-396-4}}.</ref>
It was also known as ''Barhoue''.
== Notes == <references/>
{{coord missing|France}}
[[Category:Alternative place names]] [[Category:Geography of Pyrénées-Atlantiques]] [[Category:Basque history]] [[Category:Basque toponymy]]
{{PyrénéesAtlantiques-geo-stub}}

{{otheruses}}

'''Servette''' is a [[district]] of the city of [[Geneva]], [[Switzerland]]. The district's name comes from the [[Latin]] word for forest, ''silva'', and means "little forest". Its name alludes to Servette's rural past, before Geneva grew beyond its walls and incorporated the area.

[[Image:Rue de la Servette.jpg|thumb|Rue de la Servette]]


